#: ../../articles/app_migrating.rst:53
msgid ""
"The Instance class was too generic and contained some dirty workarounds to "
"differently handle Windows and Linux images, to bootstrap an instance in a "
"number of ways, etc. To solve these problems more classes were added to the "
"*Instance* inheritance hierarchy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../articles/app_migrating.rst:58
msgid ""
"Now, base *Instance* class is abstract and agnostic of the desired OS and "
"agent type. It is inherited by two classes: *LinuxInstance* and "
"*WindowsInstance*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../articles/app_migrating.rst:61
msgid ""
"*LinuxInstance* adds a default security rule for Linux, opening a standard "
"SSH port;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../articles/app_migrating.rst:64
msgid ""
"*WindowsInstance* adds a default security rule for Windows, opening an RDP "
"port. At the same time WindowsInstance prepares a user-data allowing to use "
"Murano v1 agent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../articles/app_migrating.rst:68
msgid ""
"*LinuxInstance* is inherited by two other classes, having different software"
" config method:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../articles/app_migrating.rst:71
msgid ""
"*LinuxMuranoInstance* adds a user-data preparation to configure Murano v2 "
"agent;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../articles/app_migrating.rst:74
msgid ""
"*LinuxUDInstance* adds a custom user-data field allowing the services to "
"supply their own user data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../articles/app_migrating.rst:77
msgid ""
"You need to specify the instance type which is required by your app. It "
"specifies a field in UI, where user can select an image matched to the "
"instance type. This change must be added to UI form definition in "
"*app.name/UI/ui.yaml*."
msgstr ""

